# Component View Test

This rule applies when working on `*.view.test.tsx` files or the `tests/component-view/` framework.

## Summary

Component view tests are integration-level tests that exercise views through real Redux state using the `tests/component-view/` framework. Only Engine and allowed native modules may be mocked.

Key constraints:
- Every test must include at least one `fireEvent`, `waitFor`/`findBy`, `store.dispatch`, or Engine spy — no render scenarios
- Use selector ID constants from `ComponentName.testIds.ts`, never raw strings
- Always use `jest.config.view.js` to run tests

Run command:
```bash
yarn jest -c jest.config.view.js <path> --runInBand --silent --coverage=false
```

For the full workflow, golden rules, and code templates, read:

`.agents/skills/component-view-test/SKILL.md`

Reference files:
- `.agents/skills/component-view-test/references/writing-tests.md` (Steps 1–2)
- `.agents/skills/component-view-test/references/navigation-mocking.md` (Steps 3–4)
- `.agents/skills/component-view-test/references/reference.md` (Steps 5–7, checklist, patterns)
